{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Revise the eVED Taxation on Plug-in Hybrid Vehicles (PHEVs)",
        "additional_details": "We request specific revisions to the PHEV eVED:\r\n1. \"Fuel Duty Credit\": Allow owners to offset pump duty against their eVED bill.\r\n2. Exempt Non-Electric Miles: Use onboard tech to apply eVED only to zero-emission miles.\r\n3. Adjust the Rate: Reduce the 1.5p PHEV rate for short-range vehicles (e.g., 20-30 miles).\r\n4. \"Grandfathering Protection\": Exempt existing PHEV owners - early adopters - from the new charge.\r\nWe believe these changes would ensure fairness for those who invested in transitional green technology.",
        "background": "We call on the Government to revise the proposed eVED charge to prevent 'unfair' double taxation. PHEV drivers pay a flat 1.5p/mile even on petrol miles, where they already pay 53.95p/L fuel duty. We believe this discriminates against those who adopted hybrids in good faith to reduce emissions.",
